  "prompt": "What I can do now because my 18 year will be completed in 17 January 2017. and most companies age limit is 18 year as on aug 2016?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're concerned about missing age-related eligibility criteria for opportunities that require applicants to be 18 years old by August 2016, but you turn 18 in January 2017. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n### 1. **Double-Check the Eligibility Criteria**\n   - Some companies or organizations may have flexible deadlines or consider the age at the time of application or joining, not the time of eligibility announcement. Reach out to them directly to clarify.\n\n### 2. **Look for Opportunities Without Age Restrictions**\n   - Many programs, internships, or jobs don\u2019t have strict age limits. Focus on those that align with your skills and interests.\n\n### 3. **Prepare for Future Opportunities**\n   - Since you\u2019ll be 18 in January 2017, start preparing for opportunities that open after that date. Build your skills, network, and resume in the meantime.\n\n### 4. **Consider Age-Lax Alternatives**\n   - Look for roles in smaller companies, startups, or freelance platforms that may have more flexible age requirements.\n\n### 5. **Explore Educational or Training Programs**\n   - If work opportunities are limited, consider enrolling in courses, certifications, or training programs to enhance your qualifications for the future.\n\n### 6. **Network and Seek Advice**\n   - Connect with mentors, teachers, or professionals who can guide you on alternative paths or opportunities that don\u2019t depend on age.\n\n### 7. **Volunteer or Intern**\n   - Many organizations accept volunteers or interns regardless of age. This can help you gain experience and build your resume.\n\n### 8. **Be Honest and Persistent**\n   - If you\u2019re passionate about a specific opportunity, explain your situation and express your enthusiasm. Some organizations may make exceptions for motivated candidates.\n\nFocus on what you *can* do and start applying for opportunities that align with your age and skills. Your 18th birthday will open up many doors, so use this time to prepare and position yourself for success!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
